## Methodology

This portfolio was generated using an innovation-optimized multi-agent architecture generator:

1. **Paradigm Agent Generation**: 4 agents with radically different architectural philosophies (streaming-first, event-sourced, declarative, cross-domain wildcard) generated initial proposals in parallel.
2. **Idea Mutation**: Each proposal was mutated using randomly selected operators (invert, merge, eliminate, analogize, temporalize, abstract) to expand the solution space.
3. **Self-Refinement**: Each candidate underwent 2 rounds of self-critique to strengthen coherence and specificity without reducing ambition.
4. **Physics Critic**: A physics-of-computing critic annotated each proposal with hard constraint violations (CAP theorem, complexity bounds, network physics) without rejecting any proposals.
5. **Portfolio Assembly**: All proposals were scored on innovation, feasibility, business alignment, and migration complexity, then ranked and tiered.

The system is explicitly optimized for **architectural innovation and paradigm shifts**, not just optimization of existing patterns.
